This paper focuses on developing a methodology to monitor and evaluate web activity for cybersecurity monitoring efforts. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also deals with data analysis and anomaly detection, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of rule-based anomaly detection and predictive modeling suggests a focus on data science, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper also deals with information retrieval and search keywords, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
